---
import LayoutMinimal from "../layouts/LayoutMinimal.astro";
---

<LayoutMinimal title="Services | Ryan Eberhard" description="Fractional Product & Growth Leadership for venture-backed companies">
  <header class="header">
    <div class="header__inner">
      <a href="/" class="header__logo"><img src="/gauges-green-g-core.svg" alt="" class="header__mark" />Ryan Eberhard</a>
    </div>
    <nav class="header__nav">
      <a href="/">home</a>
      <span class="header__nav-sep">·</span>
      <a href="/experience">experience</a>
      <span class="header__nav-sep">·</span>
      <a href="/services" class="active">services</a>
      <span class="header__nav-sep">·</span>
      <a href="/log">writing</a>
      <span class="header__nav-sep">·</span>
      <a href="mailto:eberhard@gaugesgreen.com">contact</a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <!-- Intro -->
  <section class="section intro">
    <p class="item__body">
      I work with venture-backed startups when growth has stalled and the board is asking why. I start with a short diagnostic to find what's broken, then embed with your team to fix it.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <!-- What You Get -->
  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="section__title">What You Get</h2>

    <article class="item">
      <h3 class="item__title">Growth Diagnosis</h3>
      <p class="item__body">
        Features ship but revenue doesn't respond. You'll know why within two weeks.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="item">
      <h3 class="item__title">Near-Term Impact</h3>
      <p class="item__body">
        A 30/60/90 plan with specific bets, owners, and success criteria. Not a strategy deck—a shipping manifest.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="item">
      <h3 class="item__title">Hands-On Shipping</h3>
      <p class="item__body">
        I ship code alongside your engineers. PRs, not presentations.
      </p>
      <p class="item__note">
        At ZipRecruiter, I led the team that built AI matching—80% of employers got quality candidates within 24 hours, processing billions of signals across 110M job seekers.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="item">
      <h3 class="item__title">Team Assessment</h3>
      <p class="item__body">
        Clear evaluation of who's in the right seat and who isn't. Sometimes the answer is "stop hiring"—define the problem before the role.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <!-- How It Works -->
  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="section__title">How It Works</h2>

    <div class="timeline">
      <article class="timeline__phase">
        <div class="timeline__marker">1</div>
        <div class="timeline__content">
          <h3 class="item__title">Diagnostic</h3>
          <p class="timeline__duration">2–4 weeks</p>
          <p class="item__body">Deep dive into metrics, team, and blockers. You'll get a clear picture of what's broken, what's fixable, and what to do first.</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="timeline__phase">
        <div class="timeline__marker">2</div>
        <div class="timeline__content">
          <h3 class="item__title">Transformational Engagement</h3>
          <p class="timeline__duration">1–12 months</p>
          <p class="item__body">If there's a fit, I embed for a quarter and ship what actually moves the needle. Hands-on with your team, not advising from afar.</p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <!-- Who It's For -->
  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="section__title">Who It's For</h2>

    <article class="item">
      <h3 class="item__title">Series A-C Startups</h3>
      <p class="item__body">
        $2-10M ARR. Post-PMF but 2-3 quarters into the raise and the board is asking why growth isn't responding.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="item">
      <h3 class="item__title">Teams That Aren't Shipping</h3>
      <p class="item__body">
        Engineers are busy, sprints are full, but nothing moves the metrics. I help you find out why and fix it.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="item">
      <h3 class="item__title">LatAm Founders Entering US</h3>
      <p class="item__body">
        Expanding to the US market and need GTM guidance from someone who operates in both.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="item">
      <h3 class="item__title">Marketplace Businesses</h3>
      <p class="item__body">
        Two-sided platforms with supply/demand imbalance. I scaled ZipRecruiter's marketplace to 110M job seekers and 2.8M employers—these are the models I know cold.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="section__title">Let's Talk</h2>
    <p class="item__body">
      30 minutes. Whether you want a diagnostic or just want to explore fit, I'd like to hear what you're working on.
    </p>
    <p class="cta">
      <a href="/schedule">Schedule a call</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <footer class="footer">
    <a href="mailto:eberhard@gaugesgreen.com">email</a>
    <span class="header__nav-sep">·</span>
    <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/eberhard" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">linkedin</a>
    <span class="header__nav-sep">·</span>
    <a href="/schedule">book a call</a>
  </footer>
</LayoutMinimal>

<style>
  /* Sections with generous spacing */
  .section {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .section__title {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: 0 0 1em 0;
  }

  /* Items within sections */
  .item {
    margin-bottom: 2em;
  }

  .item:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .item__title {
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin: 0 0 0.5em 0;
  }

  .item__body {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .item__note {
    font-size: var(--font-size-small);
    color: var(--dim);
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 1em 0 0 0;
  }

  /* Timeline */
  .timeline {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5em;
  }

  .timeline__phase {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5em;
  }

  .timeline__marker {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 2em;
    height: 2em;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: var(--font-size-small);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--accent);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  .timeline__content {
    flex: 1;
  }

  .timeline__content .item__title {
    margin: 0 0 0.25em 0;
  }

  .timeline__duration {
    font-size: var(--font-size-small);
    color: var(--dim);
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0 0 0.75em 0;
  }

  /* CTA */
  .cta {
    margin: 1.5em 0 0 0;
  }

  .cta a {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  /* Whitespace between sections */
  hr {
    margin: 2.5em 0;
  }
</style>
